description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a state registered radiographer with either the DCR or Degree in Radiography to join our patient centred team of friendly radiology staff who are currently undergoing exciting transformational change throughout all modalities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both newly qualified and experienced staff are supported with a supernumerary period and mentor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on experience and competencies gained, Band 6 progression opportunities may be available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a very busy multi skilled department, the majority of the work will be at Russell’s Hall Acute Hospital, but there may be the opportunity to work at both the Guest and Corbett outpatient departments. You will be expected to take part in any shift systems in operation and Bank Holiday, on-call services as required, supervising and assisting other out of hours support staff, including clerical staff and radiographic helpers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to provide a high quality service and standard of imaging techniques whilst ensuring that visitors to our department receive an excellent standard of care. You will be expected to rotate through all areas of the department including theatre and mobiles, fluoroscopy, ED and general.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department also supports an Interventional Suite, Cardiac Catheter Lab, DEXA, CT and MRI, opportunities may arise for career development in these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debbie Lowe - General/ED Imaging Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: debbie.lowe2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01384 456111 ext 1255/3460&lt;/p&gt;
